1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:02,040
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,580
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,580 --> 00:00:05,140
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,380 --> 00:00:08,750
(Episode 11)

5
00:00:17,620 --> 00:00:20,560
That's it. Hurry on up.

6
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:23,660
My Jin Ju,

7
00:00:25,330 --> 00:00:26,460
no matter what happens,

8
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,870
you'll be able
to get through anything.

9
00:00:33,410 --> 00:00:34,410
Jin Ju.

10
00:00:35,810 --> 00:00:36,810
My daughter.

11
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:41,950
Dad loves you so much.

12
00:01:16,780 --> 00:01:17,780
Dad...

13
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:27,360
No.

14
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:29,830
This isn't my fault.

15
00:01:35,830 --> 00:01:37,770
It'll just be
a minor car accident, right?

16
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,510
While those two are in the hospital
and everyone's distracted,

17
00:01:41,210 --> 00:01:42,340
you'll take over the company.

18
00:01:43,610 --> 00:01:44,640
There isn't...

19
00:01:45,340 --> 00:01:47,110
more to the plan than that,
is there?

20
00:01:47,650 --> 00:01:51,020
What, are you afraid I'll kill them?

21
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:54,520
I told you,
it's nothing that serious.

22
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:57,660
Just think of it
as a minor accident...

23
00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:00,230
and brush it off.

24
00:02:01,630 --> 00:02:04,530
First, use CEO Baek's daughter
as bait...

25
00:02:04,860 --> 00:02:06,060
to lure him out.

26
00:02:28,490 --> 00:02:30,090
Once CEO Baek arrives,

27
00:02:30,690 --> 00:02:33,660
all you have to do is
quietly remove the dashcam.

28
00:02:34,830 --> 00:02:37,560
I'll handle the rest.

29
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:48,610
After you confirm
everything went as planned,

30
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:51,880
it'll all be over.

31
00:02:57,420 --> 00:02:58,420
From the very beginning...

32
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:02,120
That's it.
He planned to kill them all along.

33
00:03:05,990 --> 00:03:06,990
Dad.

34
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:25,910
Dad.

35
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:30,110
Dad!

36
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:33,820
Dad!

37
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:40,060
Dad!

38
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:42,830
Baek Jin Ju is alive?

39
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:15,560
Please, help me. Someone's hurt...

40
00:04:21,770 --> 00:04:22,770
Choi Yu Na.

41
00:04:23,770 --> 00:04:24,900
Is that you, Yu Na?

42
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:27,840
My gosh, Yu Na.

43
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:30,780
My dad is in that car.

44
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:33,810
We have to get him
out of there, Yu Na.

45
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:41,690
There's no time.
Hurry, call 911. Please!

46
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:45,460
Yu Na, please, you have to help me!

47
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:57,170
You will be at the bottom,

48
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:59,400
while Baek Jin Ju will be
at the very top.

49
00:05:00,170 --> 00:05:03,240
The two of you will be living
in completely different worlds.

50
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:08,380
Whether you accept
my proposal or not,

51
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:11,650
your decision...

52
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,750
could change both your future...

53
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,720
and Baek Jin Ju's.

54
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:22,090
Baek Jin Ju.

55
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:25,330
If Baek Jin Ju makes it out alive...

56
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:26,860
What about me?

57
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:35,110
Yu Na!

58
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:39,380
I refuse to be stuck
struggling at the bottom.

59
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:44,320
I want to soar to the very top,
way above you.

60
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:46,420
I can't...

61
00:05:47,420 --> 00:05:49,050
let it all fall apart now.

62
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,700
This isn't my fault.

63
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:04,570
Baek Jin Ju, you're the one...

64
00:06:07,310 --> 00:06:08,840
who drove me to this.

65
00:06:10,010 --> 00:06:11,080
Yu Na?

66
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,720
I'm not the one
who deserves the blame.

67
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:33,460
It's Chairman Park Tae Ho!

68
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,260
What are you doing here?

69
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:09,270
I should be asking you that.

70
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:10,900
You're a concussed patient...

71
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,670
who's supposed
to be on absolute bed rest.

72
00:07:13,470 --> 00:07:14,510
So why are you here?

73
00:07:17,510 --> 00:07:19,280
I had an important meeting.

74
00:07:19,910 --> 00:07:20,910
A meeting?

75
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:25,580
Who did you sneak out here to meet?

76
00:07:27,820 --> 00:07:28,820
Who?

77
00:07:35,060 --> 00:07:36,060
Who was it?

78
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:37,630
Director Kim.

79
00:07:44,270 --> 00:07:45,270
Sorry to keep you waiting.

80
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:48,110
Mrs. Han from Ihwachae sent me.

81
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:51,740
She said she would return the file
Ihwachae prepared on your son.

82
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,350
Ihwachae?

83
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,320
(Personal profile)

84
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:05,320
So,

85
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:07,990
the person you were
meeting here was...

86
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:11,230
I received a call from Mrs. Han
at the hospital.

87
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:16,230
It's their policy to return the file
if a client decides to pull out.

88
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:21,610
You told me to avoid Ihwachae,
so I arranged to get them here.

89
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:26,380
It's Min Jun's personal information,
so I wanted to handle it myself.

90
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:35,520
I'll be on my way then.

91
00:08:43,560 --> 00:08:44,600
But...

92
00:08:45,230 --> 00:08:46,830
why are you...

93
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:49,700
I mean, how did you know I was here?

94
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:54,010
Are you having me followed?

95
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:03,150
It's not surveillance.

96
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:06,480
Think of it as protection,
Myung Hui.

97
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:08,290
Protection?

98
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,560
Well...

99
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:16,130
Didn't you come begging
when Min Jun was a baby?

100
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:18,600
You begged me to protect
you and Min Jun.

101
00:09:19,830 --> 00:09:22,070
If I'm going to protect you two,

102
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:25,470
I have to keep my eyes on you
at all times.

103
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:31,880
You were hurt and sneaking out,
so of course I was worried.

104
00:09:32,540 --> 00:09:33,610
Right?

105
00:09:34,110 --> 00:09:37,150
I was going to send Manager Kang,

106
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:40,820
but I came
to check on you myself instead.

107
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:43,220
I see.

108
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:46,020
I'm sorry to have worried you
for nothing.

109
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:47,860
Gosh, no.

110
00:09:48,530 --> 00:09:49,530
It's fine.

111
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:05,710
Oh, hey. It's handled for now.

112
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:08,050
You can relax.

113
00:10:16,590 --> 00:10:18,660
So what about Chairman Park?

114
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:21,160
He left, but he's having
someone watch me.

115
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:25,500
By now, he's likely gotten a report
that I'm back at the hospital.

116
00:10:26,930 --> 00:10:31,470
I almost had a heart attack.
I was worried sick.

117
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,440
I was so afraid one of his lackeys
might follow you.

118
00:10:34,570 --> 00:10:37,710
I can't believe we had to use plan B
on Chairman Park himself.

119
00:10:39,580 --> 00:10:42,780
Still, I'm glad we did.
It's a good thing we were prepared.

120
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:44,950
And please thank Woo Jin for me.

121
00:10:45,780 --> 00:10:48,920
What are families for?
Of course he should help.

122
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:52,260
But what happened to Dr. Baek?

123
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:55,360
It's not like him
to stand someone up without a word.

124
00:10:56,930 --> 00:10:59,500
You don't think he had an accident,
do you?

125
00:11:03,370 --> 00:11:05,200
You planned to kill them all along.

126
00:11:06,870 --> 00:11:09,210
You used me to kill them both!

127
00:11:11,110 --> 00:11:12,480
Kill them both?

128
00:11:12,780 --> 00:11:13,780
Does that mean...

129
00:11:15,010 --> 00:11:17,010
you're certain they're both dead?

130
00:11:20,450 --> 00:11:22,920
The car exploded.
Of course they are!

131
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,060
You actually meant to kill them,

132
00:11:25,490 --> 00:11:27,560
but you tricked me into thinking
it would just be a minor accident.

133
00:11:29,830 --> 00:11:31,830
You made me get blood on my hands.

134
00:11:33,730 --> 00:11:36,230
Because of you, I...

135
00:11:36,670 --> 00:11:38,240
Unbelievable!

136
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:42,240
You're saying
some very dangerous things.

137
00:11:43,010 --> 00:11:45,610
Do you have any evidence
that I ordered you?

138
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:47,910
That's...

139
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:53,720
Framing an innocent person
without evidence is a crime!

140
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,250
And on top of that,

141
00:11:57,890 --> 00:12:00,260
you've admitted
to being an accomplice...

142
00:12:01,830 --> 00:12:03,430
to murder.

143
00:12:07,770 --> 00:12:08,870
That means...

144
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:13,340
there's a lot I can do
with this evidence.

145
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:23,550
"It's not my fault. I was used."

146
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:25,420
You can insist all you want.

147
00:12:28,090 --> 00:12:30,250
You chose to take
what belongs to Baek Jin Ju.

148
00:12:31,090 --> 00:12:33,320
This is the result
of your own choice!

149
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:38,400
And if you can't
take back that choice,

150
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:41,900
just go ahead...

151
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,000
and enjoy the things...

152
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:47,300
you've stolen.

153
00:12:52,540 --> 00:12:53,540
Move.

154
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,980
Choi Yu Na, are you still in bed?

155
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,880
What are you doing?

156
00:13:28,150 --> 00:13:30,920
Are you going through
Jin Ju's things again?

157
00:13:31,580 --> 00:13:32,620
I have to get rid of this.

158
00:13:33,620 --> 00:13:34,820
I'm going to destroy everything.

159
00:13:34,890 --> 00:13:37,120
Honestly. Are you out of your mind?

160
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:40,520
What are you going to do
when Jin Ju comes for her stuff?

161
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,470
Always so reckless.

162
00:13:49,330 --> 00:13:50,330
Good grief.

163
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:53,170
- Honey!
- What...

164
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:55,940
Honey! CEO Baek...

165
00:13:56,340 --> 00:13:58,010
- Baek...
- What is it?

166
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,110
CEO Baek...

167
00:13:59,910 --> 00:14:01,910
What about him?

168
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:04,050
What about CEO Baek?

169
00:14:04,050 --> 00:14:05,850
Did he cut your salary or something?

170
00:14:05,850 --> 00:14:07,720
No, that's not it.

171
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:08,850
What is it?

172
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:23,700
What? Seriously.
Good grief, you're killing me.

173
00:14:23,770 --> 00:14:27,400
What is it?
What happened to CEO Baek?

174
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:29,470
What's with you?

175
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:31,880
Spit it out!

176
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:35,280
Unbelievable.
What's up with you two?

177
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:37,080
A car accident?

178
00:14:37,550 --> 00:14:39,580
What about Dr. Baek? Is he okay?

179
00:14:40,220 --> 00:14:41,920
The car exploded,

180
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,990
and his daughter was with him.

181
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:50,790
You can't get involved
in Dr. Baek's affairs anymore.

182
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,960
People will get suspicious
if they find out you're acquainted.

183
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,570
But Dr. Baek...

184
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,570
You know he's the kind of person
who would understand.

185
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:01,510
Wherever he is,
he'd just want us to be okay.

186
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,070
How...

187
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:05,340
How could something
like this happen?

188
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:08,280
This is insane.
It's completely insane.

189
00:15:08,980 --> 00:15:11,420
The world must have gone mad
for this to happen.

190
00:15:12,420 --> 00:15:15,050
First, it took your innocent sister,

191
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:18,160
and now Dr. Baek too.

192
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,830
To lose such a good man
so senselessly...

193
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,900
(Adele Group)

194
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:43,150
They're ruling
CEO Baek's death a suicide?

195
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:47,690
Sudden unintended acceleration
followed by a car explosion.

196
00:15:51,460 --> 00:15:54,490
An opportunity like this
is too good to waste,

197
00:15:54,860 --> 00:15:56,260
wouldn't you agree?

198
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:59,260
We have to take full advantage
of this opportunity.

199
00:16:00,230 --> 00:16:03,400
Sir, what on earth
are you talking about?

200
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:14,450
I took the liberty of doctoring
Temi Bio's accounting ledgers.

201
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:17,080
Take this...

202
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,950
and hold a press conference.

203
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:23,220
A press conference?

204
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:28,960
CEO Baek kept secret books
and was embezzling company funds.

205
00:16:29,790 --> 00:16:33,330
You found out
and were about to report him.

206
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:35,870
That's when he panicked...

207
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,970
and killed himself,
taking his daughter with him.

208
00:16:39,370 --> 00:16:40,540
What?

209
00:16:49,450 --> 00:16:52,720
CEO Baek's suicide note will be found
in his hotel room shortly.

210
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:55,150
But sir...

211
00:16:56,850 --> 00:16:59,420
I'll acquire
the now-tarnished Temi Bio,

212
00:17:00,390 --> 00:17:03,460
and as CEO, you'll receive
a stake in Adele Group.

213
00:17:04,230 --> 00:17:05,330
Just as we originally planned,

214
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,230
let's wrap this all up neatly.

215
00:17:16,740 --> 00:17:18,040
(Confidential, Special handling)

216
00:17:20,940 --> 00:17:22,050
But...

217
00:17:23,580 --> 00:17:24,580
I mean,

218
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:26,480
isn't this...

219
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:28,950
a little extreme?

220
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,490
CEO Baek is already dead.

221
00:17:32,090 --> 00:17:34,120
He can't get in our way anymore,

222
00:17:34,830 --> 00:17:36,460
so do we really have to frame him
for fraud...

223
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:39,500
and make it look like
he killed his own daughter?

224
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:43,130
He dared...

225
00:17:44,470 --> 00:17:46,400
to look down on me.

226
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,970
There will be no deal whatsoever
with Adele Group.

227
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:52,340
Don't even think about coming
after my company again.

228
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:55,350
I have the power to expose
Adele Group's illegal activities,

229
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:57,820
and I am more than capable
of fighting back.

230
00:17:59,220 --> 00:18:00,980
Even if he's already dead,

231
00:18:01,820 --> 00:18:05,560
he must pay for treating me
like a criminal.

232
00:18:07,390 --> 00:18:10,390
I'm just paying him back in kind.

233
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:17,400
Now, get out and do your job.

234
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:20,400
Yes, sir.

235
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:37,350
I heard from our contact
in the police.

236
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:41,290
There were three explosions,
so nothing's left at the scene.

237
00:18:41,530 --> 00:18:43,630
The body was burned
beyond recognition,

238
00:18:43,630 --> 00:18:45,300
and the car was nearly incinerated.

239
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:47,660
They said forensics
won't find a thing.

240
00:18:47,930 --> 00:18:48,930
Is that so?

241
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:53,940
You used me to kill them both!

242
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,610
Kill them both?

243
00:18:55,970 --> 00:18:56,970
Does that mean...

244
00:18:57,940 --> 00:18:59,910
you're certain they're both dead?

245
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:03,180
The car exploded.
Of course they are!

246
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:07,720
We sent Choi Yu Na to confirm,
so we don't need to check anything.

247
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:11,260
Set things up so the police
can wrap up the case quickly.

248
00:19:12,890 --> 00:19:15,090
After Choi Sam Sik's press conference,

249
00:19:15,460 --> 00:19:18,630
have my wife handle the cleanup.

250
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,800
Yes, understood.

251
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:34,880
Here...

252
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,110
(Confidential, Special handling,
Financial Ledger)

253
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:39,720
is proof
of CEO Baek Jun Gi's embezzlement.

254
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:48,260
The police found a suicide note
in the hotel where he was staying,

255
00:19:48,630 --> 00:19:50,060
and everything lines up...

256
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:54,800
with my initial tip.

257
00:19:56,470 --> 00:19:57,800
What he did was wrong,

258
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:01,810
but he was my dear old friend.

259
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:06,810
Please help us
lay him to rest in peace.

260
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,880
(Temi Bio CEO Baek Jun Gi Dead)

261
00:20:08,950 --> 00:20:10,710
(CEO Choi Sam Sik
Alleges Embezzlement)

262
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:12,780
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

263
00:20:12,850 --> 00:20:15,890
They're saying he committed suicide
because of embezzlement?

264
00:20:17,020 --> 00:20:18,060
That makes no sense.

265
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,260
I know, right?

266
00:20:20,590 --> 00:20:22,230
The embezzlement evidence
and the suicide note.

267
00:20:22,430 --> 00:20:23,460
It's all suspicious.

268
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:26,700
This whole incident
is being covered up.

269
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:36,310
I knew it.

270
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:38,180
A concussion, my foot.

271
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:41,480
How dare you fake an illness
and put on a show to mess with me?

272
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:47,250
There it is again. That awful look.

273
00:20:48,450 --> 00:20:51,620
I should've just finished you off
for good back then.

274
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:54,960
Come on, that's enough.
Let's get going.

275
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:57,530
We've got a lot to do.

276
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:01,430
Consider yourself lucky today.

277
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:05,470
I'm saving my strength
so I can help the chairman.

278
00:21:05,470 --> 00:21:06,500
Do you even know?

279
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:19,980
Help the chairman?

280
00:21:20,580 --> 00:21:21,590
Hold on.

281
00:21:22,150 --> 00:21:24,690
You don't think they're involved,
do you?

282
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:26,520
That's what we should find out.

283
00:21:27,590 --> 00:21:29,290
If this incident was fabricated
and covered up,

284
00:21:29,460 --> 00:21:31,700
I know exactly
how they'll clean it up.

285
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,540
Give me an update.

286
00:21:43,540 --> 00:21:46,040
Forensics couldn't identify
the body,

287
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:48,680
and the note makes it look
like a clear-cut suicide.

288
00:21:49,180 --> 00:21:51,720
With CEO Choi requesting
a quick funeral,

289
00:21:52,020 --> 00:21:55,290
our people will have no problem
closing the case.

290
00:21:57,290 --> 00:21:59,290
Once the case is officially closed,

291
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:03,760
announce
that we're acquiring Temi Bio.

292
00:22:04,230 --> 00:22:05,930
Yes, understood.

293
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:09,670
And when you give Choi Sam Sik
his shares,

294
00:22:09,930 --> 00:22:11,370
make sure he keeps his mouth shut.

295
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:14,140
Should I warn him
about what Choi Yu Na did?

296
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:19,040
We can play
the Choi Yu Na card later.

297
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:22,750
Right now, he's docile
because he wants the shares.

298
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:27,050
But if he ever objects
or tries to blackmail me later,

299
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:31,490
I'll tell him his daughter was
an accomplice to murder.

300
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:35,190
That's why I used her
in the first place.

301
00:22:35,460 --> 00:22:36,460
I see.

302
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:41,500
By the way, what about Min Jun?

303
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,040
Just leave him be.

304
00:22:48,670 --> 00:22:51,840
He won't throw his life away
and abandon his own mother...

305
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:55,810
over some girl.

306
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:01,990
In time,

307
00:23:02,990 --> 00:23:04,450
he'll forget all about it.

308
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,210
I'm here about the accident victims.

309
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:25,210
Where's Baek Jin Ju?

310
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:26,280
You must mean...

311
00:23:26,510 --> 00:23:28,850
the driver and passenger
if you're referring to the victims.

312
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:32,380
The car exploded, so we couldn't
even recover the bodies.

313
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:34,550
They were transported
along with the vehicle wreckage.

314
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,160
Jin Ju...

315
00:23:41,020 --> 00:23:43,360
No, this can't be happening.

316
00:23:44,090 --> 00:23:46,660
I'm sorry, but CCTV
from a nearby road confirmed...

317
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:49,800
that the two of them
were traveling together.

318
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:53,640
And the driver's suicide note
clearly states the motive.

319
00:23:55,210 --> 00:23:56,270
A suicide?

320
00:23:56,370 --> 00:23:58,140
That's why
we're wrapping things up here,

321
00:23:58,480 --> 00:23:59,610
so you should head back.

322
00:24:08,220 --> 00:24:09,720
The driver committed suicide?

323
00:24:11,890 --> 00:24:13,520
That's impossible.

324
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:17,630
How could he do that to Jin Ju?

325
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:29,370
This can't be right.

326
00:24:45,990 --> 00:24:49,530
It must've been burning hot.
How could you have been in there?

327
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:55,970
I never even got to say I was sorry.

328
00:24:58,770 --> 00:25:01,100
There was so much...

329
00:25:02,610 --> 00:25:04,610
I wanted to tell you.

330
00:25:50,620 --> 00:25:52,420
What do I do?

331
00:26:07,570 --> 00:26:09,340
This whole thing is so messed up.

332
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,850
When something
is burned black like this,

333
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:21,350
it's impossible to forget.

334
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:27,490
Baek Jin Ju.

335
00:26:36,430 --> 00:26:40,340
(Last night)

336
00:26:49,910 --> 00:26:51,580
Jin Ju. Baek Jin Ju.

337
00:26:53,180 --> 00:26:54,720
My daughter, you have to get up.

338
00:27:01,860 --> 00:27:03,730
Jin Ju, you can't stay here.

339
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:05,900
You'll be in danger too.

340
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,800
Hurry, get out of here.

341
00:27:55,810 --> 00:27:57,310
Help me.

342
00:28:00,050 --> 00:28:01,720
Please, help me.

343
00:28:04,020 --> 00:28:05,490
Over on the road...

344
00:28:07,020 --> 00:28:08,630
My dad is...

345
00:28:10,360 --> 00:28:12,030
Please.

346
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:16,500
Please, can somebody help me?

347
00:28:18,230 --> 00:28:19,440
Dad...

348
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:22,610
Dad...

349
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:41,260
Dad.

350
00:29:08,620 --> 00:29:09,620
Dad.

351
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:13,120
Where's Dad?

352
00:29:17,690 --> 00:29:21,230
News about Temi Bio
is making major waves.

353
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:24,430
Following CEO Baek Jun Gi's
sudden accident,

354
00:29:24,630 --> 00:29:26,540
Korean branch head Choi Sam Sik...

355
00:29:26,540 --> 00:29:28,270
held a press conference alleging...

356
00:29:28,270 --> 00:29:30,640
that CEO Baek had embezzled
company funds.

357
00:29:31,070 --> 00:29:33,440
We now turn
to CEO Choi Sam Sik's statement.

358
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,110
Here is proof...

359
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:39,220
of CEO Baek Jun Gi's embezzlement.

360
00:29:39,550 --> 00:29:40,620
(Choi's Press Conference
Makes Headlines)

361
00:29:40,620 --> 00:29:41,720
(Evidence
of Baek's Embezzlement Found)

362
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:50,090
The police found a suicide note
in the hotel where he was staying,

363
00:29:50,730 --> 00:29:51,900
and everything lines up...

364
00:29:53,300 --> 00:29:55,630
with my initial tip.

365
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:58,300
With reports
of Baek Jun Gi's accident...

366
00:29:58,300 --> 00:30:00,400
and embezzlement allegations
surfacing,

367
00:30:00,470 --> 00:30:02,170
- That's ridiculous.
- the case is growing more complex.

368
00:30:02,540 --> 00:30:04,940
Police are investigating
the cause of the crash...

369
00:30:04,940 --> 00:30:06,310
and reviewing CEO Choi's statement.

370
00:30:06,740 --> 00:30:09,280
We will provide updates
as we learn more.

371
00:30:16,150 --> 00:30:18,350
Chairman Park took over Temi Bio.

372
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:20,960
It's like
this was his plan all along.

373
00:30:22,130 --> 00:30:25,600
If Dr. Baek's accident was staged,
like we suspected,

374
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:27,160
then...

375
00:30:28,060 --> 00:30:30,300
Oh Jung Ran will clean it up
the way she does best.

376
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:51,690
Make sure everyone
who helped us this time...

377
00:30:52,190 --> 00:30:53,360
keeps their mouth shut.

378
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:55,090
How much longer...

379
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:57,390
do we have to keep
doing things like this?

380
00:30:57,830 --> 00:30:59,130
Why are you chickening out
on me again?

381
00:30:59,430 --> 00:31:00,760
But someone died this time!

382
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:02,770
Lower your voice.

383
00:31:07,270 --> 00:31:09,470
Stop having second thoughts
and just do your job.

384
00:31:10,610 --> 00:31:13,010
Until Hyun Jun becomes
the head of Adele Group,

385
00:31:13,980 --> 00:31:15,710
there's nothing I won't do
to stay...

386
00:31:16,210 --> 00:31:17,680
on Chairman Park's good side.

387
00:31:19,250 --> 00:31:21,480
No matter how many die,
we push forward.

388
00:31:22,050 --> 00:31:23,050
Got it?

389
00:31:44,510 --> 00:31:45,810
Following CEO Baek's death,

390
00:31:45,810 --> 00:31:49,310
the embezzlement case will be closed
due to a lack of prosecution.

391
00:31:49,780 --> 00:31:52,780
Amid the turmoil,
Adele Chairman Park Tae Ho...

392
00:31:52,850 --> 00:31:53,950
- Adele.
- is stepping in...

393
00:31:53,950 --> 00:31:56,190
to resolve the situation
by acquiring Temi Bio.

394
00:31:56,550 --> 00:31:57,790
Chairman Park Tae Ho?

395
00:32:03,290 --> 00:32:05,330
- Jin Ju!
- Dad!

396
00:32:14,100 --> 00:32:16,740
Dad!

397
00:32:18,980 --> 00:32:20,280
It's Chairman Park Tae Ho!

398
00:32:27,050 --> 00:32:28,120
Park Tae Ho...

399
00:32:44,830 --> 00:32:47,040
(Confidential, Special handling)

400
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:56,950
(Pearl in Red)

401
00:32:57,150 --> 00:33:00,350
Now that you have your wings,
you must fly to the very top.

402
00:33:00,350 --> 00:33:03,690
I'll make
what I took from Jin Ju mine.

403
00:33:03,690 --> 00:33:06,360
That greed can consume you
and make you a monster, you know.

404
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:08,120
You have to be a monster
so people...

405
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:10,330
don't take what's yours
and walk all over you.

406
00:33:10,330 --> 00:33:14,060
- All I have left is revenge.
- I'm sorry, Dad.

407
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:17,370
And my revenge begins
by killing the person I used to be.

408
00:33:17,370 --> 00:33:19,370
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
